\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Install copper foil around the HV pigtail.
 Foil can also be used to minimize the gap in the shielding at the ground
 break insulator and shield around the filter end cap.
 Kapton tape cover the resistor lead can prevent undesired shorts allowing
 the shield to be nearly complete.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Install shield braid around the HV pigtail covering the entire length of
 the cable, including the connector, and extend up around to filter end
 cap to contact the tube.
 The braid can be bunched up to go around the filter tube and stretched
 out to be snug around the cable.
 Conductive epoxy can be used to ensure a solid electrical connection to
 the tube for contact the shield braid around the HV connector pigtail.
 Do not attempt to solder connections to the tube or the 3D printed plastic
 parts will melt.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Solder the ground wire with connector to the HV pigtail connector end of
 the shield braid.
\end_layout

